Building with MinGW/MSYS:
    Build libmc--c:
    set HOME environment variable to your development home directory
    extract libmc--c to $HOME/
    cd libmc--c
    make
    make install
    
    Build test app:
    cd test
    make


Using:
    Copy terrain.png to $HOME/libmc--c/bin.
    Copy shared libraries to $HOME/libmc--c/bin:
        DevIL.dll
        ILU.dll
        ILUT.dll
        libgcc
        libstdc++
        sfml-graphics.dll
        sfml-system.dll
        sfml-window.dll
    
    cd $HOME/libmc--c/bin
    mc--c
    
    This test program will preview how each block will look with this skin,
    using libmc--c.
    
Controls:
    Zoom        Mouse-wheel scroll, PageUp, PageDown
    Move        Left-click drag, arrow keys, WASD
    Turn        Right-click drag, Home, End
    Respawn     Middle-click
    Tree color  R, G, B

Thanks to the following people for testing:
    vLK
